# MOST IMPORTANT RULE

ALL CONFIGURATION MUST COME FROM .ENV FILES.

NO HARDCODED VALUES.

NO HARDCODED PASSWORDS.

NO HARDCODED API KEYS.

NO HARDCODED URLS.

NO HARDCODED DATABASE SETTINGS.

EVERYTHING MUST BE CONFIGURABLE THROUGH .ENV.

The application must work immediately after the developer fills the required .env values.

Every service must contain:

.env.example

and must load configuration from environment variables.

